JOHANNESBURG The chairperson, a board member and the chief financial officer of the Lewis Group have announced they are leaving the retailer.This announcement follows a 36 percent decline in headline earnings per share.Lewis chairperson David Nurek told the board he plans to retire after serving as a director and chairman since the group s listing on the JSE in 2004.READ: Lewis refunds R67m in loss-of-employment insurance policiesThe furniture giant said operating costs were contained to an increase of only 5.5 percent.Two years ago, the Lewis Group suffered a setback after it had to refund R44-million to a group of customers because it sold loss of employment insurance to customers not eligible for such cover.eNCA